	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I cut board traces all the time. Just use a blade and keep going over the trace until it tests open with a meter. If you cut the wrong trace or need to re-bridge it later, just scratch the coating off on either side of the cut, then put a bit of solder and it will bridge across. Often you can cut the trace right next to a soldered wire, making it easier to re-bridge later. The point is that armed with a meter, blade, and solder, you can reliably diagnose and correct any damage you make.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


