		<td><b>SMD Resistor Fix</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've been noticing a lot of the graphics glitches lately. I did the resistor fix with SMD resistors. The closest the local store had was 150 ohm so I used those. The SMD resistors are so small that the case fits perfectly without modification. All the graphics glitches are gone and the PowerPak works fine. If anybody wants I can post a picture. You have to cut a trace on the component side for connector 6.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


